    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has caramelised, add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add 700ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1.1L] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, <strong>beef stock mix</strong>,<strong> Henderson's Relish</strong> and the <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>bacon lardons</strong> to the pot, and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and simmer for 5 min or until the soup has thickened, then take the pot off the heat</p>",
